        </tabs>
        |<div class="image">{{Icon|Name=Dialogue-{{{Frame}}}-Icon|Size=60|Link=1}}</div>
        <div class="content">
            <div class="character">{{{Character}}}</div>
            <div class="text">{{{Content 1|}}}</div>
        </div>
        }}
    </div>
    }}
</div>
</includeonly>

<noinclude>
== Description ==
This template is __Gallery__. It is use to create the panel for a line of dialogue. <br />
'''Character''' is the parameter for the name of the character. <br />
'''Frame''' is the frame of the character. It is for the dialogue icon. <br />
<br />
'''Content''' is to write what the character said during the dialogue. <br />
The '''Choice''' are if there is a dialogue option.
<br />
This template has 2 different layout, one if it is a ''Character'' and the other one if it is the ''Narrator''.<br />
Just write ''Narrator'' if it is him.<br />  

== Code ==
{{Dialogue
|Character= <!--If The character is the Narrator, then you just have to use the Content 1-->
|Frame=
|+ <!--Fill for each Choice available (no need to use Choice 1 if there is only one choice)-->
|Choice 1=
|Content 1=
|Choice 2=
|Content 2=
|Choice 3=
|Content 3=
|}}
